5_26	0.33033847	&UR; &LR; The line-item veto struck down Thursday allowed a president to sign a statute into law, but then, within five days, cancel certain items in the legislation.
5_27	0.18414486	Congress could in turn reinstate the item by passing a separate bill, which it did in 38 of the instances in which Clinton exercised the power.
5_28	0.14311141	The court, however, found that the ``Presentment Clause'' was crafted in a deliberate fashion.
